President Alassane Ouattara, visiting
injured people at the hospital, called the incident a national tragedy 
and said an investigation was underway to determine what happened.

A Reuters correspondent said blood stains and abandoned shoes littered the scene outside the stadium on Tuesday morning.

'My two children came here yesterday.
I told them not to come but they didn't listen. They came when I was 
sleeping. What will I do?' said Assetou Toure, a cleaner.

