She did not know if her children had escaped unhurt.

The incident was the worst of its 
kind in Abidjan since 2010, when a stampede at a stadium during a 
football match killed 18 people.

Ivory Coast, once a stable economic 
hub for West Africa, is struggling to recover from a 2011 civil war in 
which more than 3,000 people were killed.

